                        RHEL</h1>
                    <h1 class="display-6 mt-5">Repositorios y paquetes escenciales 🔧</h1>
                    <p>1 - Actualizamos el S.O y sus paquetes:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">sudo dnf update && dnf upgrade -y</code></pre>
                    <p>2 - Agregamos el repositorio EPEL:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">sudo dnf install epel-release -y</code></pre>
                    <p>3 - Instalamos paquetes escenciales:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">sudo dnf install dnf-utils nano tree curl wget btop traceroute iproute telnet nmap tcpdump iputils unzip tar git rsync util-linux-user nfs-utils bind-utils -y</code></pre>
                    <h1 class="display-6 mt-5">Activar rpmfusion 🔧</h1>
                    <p>4 - habilitar el repositorio CRB:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">sudo dnf config-manager --set-enabled crb</code></pre>
                    <p>5 - Importar EPEL y EPEL Next Repository:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">
						dnf install \
							https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/epel-release-latest-9.noarch.rpm \
							https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/epel-next-release-latest-9.noarch.rpm -y
					</code></pre>
                    <p>6 - Instale RPM Fusion Free:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">sudo dnf install --nogpgcheck https://mirrors.rpmfusion.org/free/el/rpmfusion-free-release-$(rpm -E %rhel).noarch.rpm -y</code></pre>
                    <p>7 - Instale RPM Fusion No Free:</p>
                    <pre class=""><code class="language-bash">sudo dnf install --nogpgcheck https://mirrors.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/el/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$(rpm -E %rhel).noarch.rpm -y</code></pre>
